# wolfRadar — daily snapshot scheduler examples
#
# The job runs: backend/scripts/run-daily-snapshot.sh
# It builds SQLite screener snapshot + Wolf Ratings for the full universe.
# Resume-safe: interrupted runs continue on the next invocation (skips symbols already stored for today).
#
# --- crontab (Linux / macOS) ---
#
# Edit: crontab -e
#
# 11:00 UTC Mon–Fri (~6:00 AM US Eastern, before market open)
# Adjust hour for your timezone.
#
# 0 11 * * 1-5 /Users/alexandrakita/wolfRadar/backend/scripts/run-daily-snapshot.sh
#
# Optional: force full recompute every Sunday 05:00 UTC
# 0 5 * * 0 /Users/alexandrakita/wolfRadar/backend/scripts/run-daily-snapshot.sh --force
#
# --- macOS launchd (recommended on Mac) ---
#
# 1. Copy and edit the plist path:
#    cp scripts/com.wolfradar.snapshot.plist.example ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.wolfradar.snapshot.plist
# 2. Load:
#    launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.wolfradar.snapshot.plist
# 3. Test run:
#    launchctl start com.wolfradar.snapshot
# 4. Logs:
#    backend/logs/snapshot-YYYY-MM-DD.log
#
# --- verify ---
#
# curl http://127.0.0.1:3333/api/screener/status
# rowCount should be ~6381 after a successful full run
